Discriminant variables are evaluated with the two-sided Fisher's exact test. Differences between three groups were analyzed by means of a repeated-measures oneway ANOVA followed by a Fisher's post hoc test. We used the Cox proportional hazards ratios (HR) and 95% CI for the end points.
